---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Breadcrumbs from '../components/nav/Breadcrumbs.astro';
import { breadcrumbs } from '../lib/jsonld';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Methodology: How AIStudio Verifies Every Fact"
  description="How AIStudio keeps its AI model database accurate: official sources only, per-fact citations with verification dates, automated staleness checks, and public data on GitHub."
  jsonld={[breadcrumbs([{ name: 'Methodology' }])]}
>
  <Breadcrumbs items={[{ label: 'Methodology' }]} />

  <article class="prose-site max-w-2xl pb-8" data-pagefind-body>
    <h1 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight sm:text-3xl">How we verify data</h1>

    <p class="mt-6">
      The AI industry changes monthly and most "AI model comparison" content is stale or invented.
      AIStudio exists to be the boring, correct alternative. These are the rules the whole site
      runs on:
    </p>

    <h2>1. Official sources only</h2>
    <p>
      Every price, context window, model ID, and release date is taken from the vendor's own
      documentation, pricing page, or announcement, never from aggregators, social posts, or
      memory. Each fact stores the exact URL it came from.
    </p>

    <h2>2. Per-fact citations with dates</h2>
    <p>
      Facts on this site carry a superscript source number and a "verified" date, the day we last
      checked that number against its source. The full source list appears at the bottom of every
      model page.
    </p>

    <h2>3. Benchmark provenance is labeled</h2>
    <p>
      Benchmark scores are marked "vendor" when published by the model's own maker and
      "third-party" when reported by someone else (including competitors' cross-evals). Eval
      harness and effort settings vary between reporters, so we keep methodology notes on each
      benchmark page and advise against reading small deltas as meaningful.
    </p>

    <h2>4. Automated staleness checks</h2>
    <p>
      A weekly automated job flags any fact not re-verified within 90 days and opens a public
      issue. Data that can't be re-verified gets removed rather than left to rot.
    </p>

    <h2>5. Public data</h2>
    <p>
      The entire database is a set of human-readable files in a
      <a href="https://github.com/ParishKhan/aistudio" rel="noopener">public GitHub repository</a>.
      If you find an error, open an issue; corrections ship the same day whenever possible.
    </p>

    <h2>What we don't do</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>No affiliate placements or paid rankings, ever.</li>
      <li>No auto-generated filler pages: thin pages are skipped rather than published.</li>
      <li>No numbers without sources: if we can't cite it, we don't publish it.</li>
    </ul>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
